                                                                                                               Welfare home head held for abuse
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Shimla, March 19: Three teachers and the principal of welfare home for the physically challenged aided by the Himchal government have been arrested for allegedly raping inmates, between 13 and 21 years old.        
	The case  which comes weeks after the death of medical college student Aman Satya Kachru from injuries suffered during ragging  came to light after some of the six victims told another student about the abuse.        
	Shikha Sood, 23, doing a speech therapy course at the centre and going back home every day unlike the victims who stay there, recounted the horrific tales to her mother, who informed a police officer living near her home.        
	The medical report of two of the victims have confirmed rape. The rest are awaited, after which the accused will be produced in court.         
	Principal Vijay Singh, 27, co-ordinator Dinesh, 22, and teacher Amarjeet Singh, 22, were picked up yesterday. The third teacher, Vinod, 28, surrendered today, Shimla police chief R.M. Sharma said.        
	Chief minister Prem Kumar Dhumal dubbed the incidents shameful and ordered a probe.         
	Established in 2004, the Prerna Welfare Association has 27 students  12 boys and 15 girls  of which five do not stay there. The others are housed on the same floor with male teachers. The lady hostel warden has been on leave for two months. There are no guards.        
	The inmates at the centre, which gets Rs 30,000 a month under the Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan, claimed they had no medical check-up in four years.                                                                                                                                                                            
